Patch Set 6:

I think Michael raised a good question. My concern is if we use glanceclient here, is it ok to let the server depending on the client?

Patch Set 6:

Yeah, Michael brings up a good question. Although I think it's tangential to this PR, as the PR isn't adding any dependencies. 

I have wondered if glance-replicator doesn't really belong with glance server. Among other things, glance has a rather (understandably) large test suite and these tests don't help much for a CLI tool. I've wondered if this tool should be in python-glanceclient or even a separate package...

Thus, I changed it in patch set 7 to reraise the exception if the slave token is not missing.
